textBeforeTable: The Matchup Navy Heads To Kinston For Fourth Annual Freedom Classic The Navy baseball team will continue its early season road action with a three-game set of games in Kinston, N.C. versus Air Force in the 2014 Freedom Classic. The two teams have faced off at historic Grainger Stadium since 2011 and have split those 10 games evenly at 5-5. @NavyAthletics Twitter Updates Fri. | Sat. | Sun. textAfterTable: Navy vs. Air Force The Midshipmen are 17-18 all-time versus the Falcons. Navy is currently on a one-game losing streak versus Air Force. Last 10 meetings (5-5)... 2/24/13 at Kinston, N.C., L, 13-3 2/24/13 at Kinston, N.C., W, 3-2 2/23/13 at Kinston, N.C., L, 8-7 2/22/13 at Kinston, N.C., W, 3-1 2/26/12 at Kinston, N.C., W, 7-4 2/25/12 at Kinston, N.C., L, 10-4 2/25/12 at Kinston, N.C., L 8-7 (10) 2/27/11 at Kinston, N.C., W, 13-3 2/26/11 at Kinston, N.C., W, 6-4 2/25/11 at Kinston, N.C., L, 8-2 Mids & Falcons, Last Series During the weekend of Feb. 22-24, 2013, the Mids and Falcons faced off for the third consecutive year in Kinston, N.C. for the Freedom Classic. The two squads split a four-game series with each team alternating wins. Current Jr. Anthony Parenti and recent grad Ben Nelson led the Navy pitching staff with 15.0 combined innings and only one earned run allowed. Individually, Parenti struck out a career-high nine Falcons in Game One of Sunday's (2/24) DH, while Nelson countered with eight strike outs in Friday's (2/22) opening win. Offensively, Brad Borosak drove in a team-high three RBIs over the series. As a team, Air Force outhit Navy, 34-27 and outscored the Mids, 24-16. Navy versus the Mountain West Conference (MWC) The Mids have an all-time record of 17-22-1 versus current members of the MWC: 17-18 vs. Air Force, 0-3-1 vs. New Mexico and 0-1 vs. Fresno State.
